==English==

=== Etymology ===
French ''parlement'', debating(-chamber); ''parler'', to speak.

Tamil ''par-alu-mandram''. ''par'' is People, ''alum'' is Ruling, ''mandram'' is Council. Thus Council that rules the People

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# Institution whose elected or appointed members meet to debate the major political issues of the day and to exercise legislative powers, and in some cases executive or judicial powers also.
# (by extension) the collective noun for a group of [[rook]]s {{italbrac|the species of bird}} or [[owl]]s.

